all = {'one': ('a', 'b', 'c'), 'two': ('x', 'y', 'z'), 'local': 'internals',
    'sub': {'page': ('e', 'f', 'g'), 'name': 'name'}}
find_all = {'sample.one': ('a', 'b', 'c'), 'sample.two': ('x', 'y', 'z'),
    'sample.local': ('internals',), 'sample.sub.page': ('e', 'f', 'g'),
    'sample.sub.name': ('name',)}
find_reverse = {'a': 'sample.one', 'b': 'sample.one', 'c': 'sample.one',
    'x': 'sample.two', 'y': 'sample.two', 'z': 'sample.two', 'internals':
    'sample.local', 'e': 'sample.sub.page', 'f': 'sample.sub.page', 'g':
    'sample.sub.page', 'name': 'sample.sub.name'}
_all, reverse = rearrange('sample', all)
assert _all == find_all
assert reverse == find_reverse
all = {'.one': ('a', 'b', 'c'), '.two': ('x', 'y', 'z'), '.local':
